# Render static-site rewrites — proxy API paths to the Go backend
# service, then fall through to /index.html for SPA routes.
#
# Why this exists:
#   The static site (this service) and the Go API are two separate
#   Render services on different .onrender.com subdomains. Without
#   these proxy rules, requests to API endpoints — including the
#   `/m/<short>` share-link redirector and the `/og/m/<short>.png`
#   matchup preview renderer — hit the static site and fall through
#   to the SPA's catch-all, which serves the React index.html and
#   then React Router's `path="*"` Navigate-to-home rule fires.
#   Visible symptom: matchup share links unfurl with the marketing
#   card and clicking them redirects to /home.
#
# Render evaluates rules top to bottom; the first match wins. So
# every API-path rule has to land BEFORE the SPA fallback at the
# bottom. The 200 status code is the rewrite (proxy) opcode —
# the user's URL bar stays at matchup-uud5.onrender.com; only the
# response body comes from the API service.

# --- Short-URL share gateway (Go API: /m/{short} + /b/{short}) ---
# These are the URLs the in-app ShareButton generates. The API
# handler crawler-detects + serves OG HTML to crawlers and 302's
# humans to the long SPA path.
/m/*                                    https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/m/:splat                                    200
/b/*                                    https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/b/:splat                                    200

# --- Dynamic OG image renderers ---
# `/og/m/<short>.png` and `/og/b/<short>.png` are the image URLs
# embedded in the OG HTML's <meta og:image>. iMessage/Slack fetch
# these directly; if the proxy is missing the unfurl falls back to
# /og-default.png (the marketing card).
/og/*                                   https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/og/:splat                                   200

# --- Health + ops endpoints ---
# /health is the only one a user might curl; /metrics + /share/landed
# are internal. All return non-HTML.
/health                                 https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/health                                      200
/metrics                                https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/metrics                                     200
/share/landed                           https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/share/landed                                200

# --- Admin maintenance jobs ---
# POST /admin/jobs/* — owner triggers reconciliation etc. via the
# browser's DevTools console while signed in.
/admin/jobs/*                           https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/admin/jobs/:splat                           200

# --- Apple App Site Association + Android Asset Links ---
# Both files have to live at the app's primary domain or the OS
# claim-resolution fails. The Go handlers read the JSON template
# from env, so the file content needs to come from the API.
/.well-known/*                          https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/.well-known/:splat                          200

# --- Server-Sent Event streams ---
# Activity bell push: one persistent connection per signed-in user.
# Bracket round-advance: live update during timer-driven brackets.
# Both must reach the API for the SSE handler to run.
/users/me/activity/events               https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/users/me/activity/events                    200
/brackets/:id/events                    https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/brackets/:id/events                         200

# --- ConnectRPC service paths ---
# Every RPC the SPA makes lives at /<package>.v1.<Service>/<Method>.
# Listed individually rather than via a catch-all so we don't
# accidentally proxy SPA routes that happen to contain a dot.
/auth.v1.*                              https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/auth.v1.:splat                              200
/matchup.v1.*                           https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/matchup.v1.:splat                           200
/bracket.v1.*                           https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/bracket.v1.:splat                           200
/community.v1.*                         https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/community.v1.:splat                         200
/activity.v1.*                          https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/activity.v1.:splat                          200
/user.v1.*                              https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/user.v1.:splat                              200
/home.v1.*                              https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/home.v1.:splat                              200
/admin.v1.*                             https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/admin.v1.:splat                             200
/search.v1.*                            https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/search.v1.:splat                            200
/upload.v1.*                            https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/upload.v1.:splat                            200
/comment.v1.*                           https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/comment.v1.:splat                           200
/like.v1.*                              https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/like.v1.:splat                              200
/report.v1.*                            https://matchup-vhl6.onrender.com/report.v1.:splat                            200

# --- SPA fallback (must stay LAST) ---
# Every other path is a React Router route; serve index.html and
# let the SPA handle it client-side. Status 200 (not 302) so the
# URL bar stays on the requested path; React Router reads it on
# mount and renders the right component.
/*                                      /index.html                                                                   200
